   <abstract>Cherokee Textile Mills was founded in Knoxville, Tennessee in 1917. It produced fine cotton goods on a contract basis. The Mill moved from Knoxville to Sevierville, Tennessee, in 1954 as a result of Sevierville's 1951 decision to issue revenue bonds to attract nonlocal business.</abstract>
